The paper deals with binary classification, which is a core topic in machine learning, and proposes a new algorithm for handling abstention in the bounded-rate setting. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also involves theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithm, which suggests it could be relevant to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses empirical comparisons to evaluate the algorithm, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics) sub-categories.
